  "rationale": "The esentutl.exe process is suspicious because it is used with the /vss flag to copy the SAM hive from C:\\windows\\system32\\config to C:\\ProgramData\\SAM, a common technique for credential dumping, and it also connects to the \\lsass named pipe, indicating potential interaction with the Local Security Authority Subsystem Service."
